Former Senator representing Kaduna Central, Shehu Sani, has said that some communities in the Northwest states ravaged by banditry and terrorism sold their votes for mere packs of Spaghetti and noodles. “Some communities in the North West ravaged by terrorists and Bandits were bought over to vote, after being shared packets of Spaghetti and ‘Indomie’, in the absence of cash. They literally ate their freedom.” he tweeted on Tuesday.